    <div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='7685#1257367893'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2009-11-04T20:51:33+00:00">Nov 4, 2009 08:51 PM UTC</time> by <b>Arvind Gopu</b><a class="anchor" name="1257367893">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>I have not seen any questions from the security team or from Alain.

I talked to Anand, and he said it would be ok to close this ticket. He said he will bring this up in the next security meeting as necessary. He also confirmed that running the probes once an hour suffices.

Closing this ticket.
-ag</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='7685#1256837402'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2009-10-29T17:30:02+00:00">Oct 29, 2009 05:30 PM UTC</time> by <b>Arvind Gopu</b><a class="anchor" name="1256837402">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>Security team (and Alain cc&#39;ed -- to whom only one resource discussed below &#34;SECMON_CADIST_VDT&#34; applies),

Most of you may remember Anand Padmanabhan of the security team wrote a bunch of RSV probes that monitor the CA certs/CRLs&#39; content as well as retrieval mechanisms. This is documented here&#58; <a href='https&#58;//twiki.grid.iu.edu/bin/view/Security/CentralizedRSVSecurityProbe' target='_blank' rel='nofollow'>https&#58;//twiki.grid.iu.edu/bin/view/Security/CentralizedRSVSecurityProbe</a>

Anand has been running a test instance of these probes on an RSV client hosted at NCSA.

Now, we have set these up at the GOC. As usual, the results are viewable via MyOSG&#58;

Resource_Group summary&#58; <a href='http&#58;//tinyurl.com/yzoaraa' target='_blank' rel='nofollow'>http&#58;//tinyurl.com/yzoaraa</a>

Resource_Group Current Status&#58; <a href='http&#58;//myosg.grid.iu.edu/rgcurrentstatus/index?datasource=currentstatus&rg=on&rg_257=on' target='_blank' rel='nofollow'>http&#58;//myosg.grid.iu.edu/rgcurrentstatus/index?datasource=currentstatus&rg=on&rg_257=on</a>

Seven-day RG history&#58; <a href='http&#58;//myosg.grid.iu.edu/rgstatushistory/index?datasource=statushistory&start_type=7daysago&end_type=today&rg=on&rg_257=on' target='_blank' rel='nofollow'>http&#58;//myosg.grid.iu.edu/rgstatushistory/index?datasource=statushistory&start_type=7daysago&end_type=today&rg=on&rg_257=on</a>

-------------------------------

NOTES&#58;

-- Note that the above setup is based on virtual/fake resources (with fake FQDNs that are not network-accessible) and services defined in OIM. This helps us leverage the service-monitoring features of RSV in the OIM/MyOSG architecture.

--- OSG_SECURITY_MONITOR is the resource group name that groups four resources (at this time)&#58;

1) Secmon_Cadist_goc - four probes monitor the expiry state of CAs, the iGTF synchronization status, YUM update and VDT-updater retrieval status on the OSG CA repo hosted by the GOC
2) Secmon_Cadist_vdt - four probes monitor the expiry state of CAs, the iGTF synchronization status, YUM update and VDT-updater retrieval status on the VDT CA repo hosted by the VDT
3) Secmon_Crl - three probes monitor the fetch-crl mechanism, the cron job that runs fetch-crl, and the expiry state of the CRLs themselves
4) Secmon_Voms - one probe that monitors the availability of VOMS servers defined in the OSG VO package.

-- There are no alarm/notification mechanism attached to the above MyOSG view at this time. However, we (GOC) have plans to include an event handler as part of our larger ticket-handling project that can be used to trigger notifications (I am not going to go into further detail here since it&#39;s out of scope). We hope to have that feature enabled by mid/end of winter 2009-10.

---  In the meanwhile, if you (security team or VDT) wish to --  feel free to grab the XML equivalent of the current status, and setup a simple script based notification mechanism that alerts you if something goes wrong.

-- Right now the contacts for the virtual resources do not really matter all that much, not in any automated infrastructure. But ... Per Rob&#39;s recommendation, I have made&#58;
1) the security team as the primary admin contact, and
2) the GOC as the secondary admin contact
3) Mine Altunay as primary security contact
<div id='show_785247597' class=''><button class="btn">Show More</button></div><div class='detail hidden' id='detail_785247597'>4) Rob Quick as secondary security contact.
--- Security team/VDT, please let us know if those contacts are not appropriate. The GOC will use those contacts manually to notify problem conditions to the appropriate contact.

-- Anand/Security team, we still need to work out some minor details -- how often what probe needs to be run, etc. Also, I urge you to update the above twiki doc with a reference to the production results on MyOSG.

-- Anand, I have updated the probes a bit to work in the GOC setup. The changes are in the trunk if you wanted to take a look. Also, I will be happy to explain over a phone call the major edits.

Please let me know if you have any questions.

Cheers,
-ag

Ticket-meta - assigning to all three GOC support members FYI.
